******
[2] Beijing
Date: Thu 6 2014
Source: Xinhua News Agency [edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/china/2014-02/06/c_133095625.htm


Beijing has confirmed this year's [2014] 2nd human case of the H7N9 bird flu, the local health authority said on Thursday [6 Feb 2014]. The patient, who was still in critical condition Thursday, had raised, traded and slaughtered live poultry before falling ill, the Beijing municipal health and family planning commission said in a press release. The document said the case was confirmed by the municipal disease prevention and control center on Wednesday [5 Feb 2014], but did not identify the patient.

The capital city's 1st human H7N9 case was reported on [24 Jan 2014]. The patient, a man, had reportedly bought pigeons and eaten them before testing positive for H7N9 bird flu.

[editor: Lu Hui]

